        "description": {
            "value": "<p>This chime's carvings depict skulls and other grim icons. When activated, it creates an aura of <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Fear]{Fear}</em> in a @Template[type:emanation|distance:5] for 1 round. Creatures in the aura must attempt a <span data-pf2-check=\"will\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,magical,uncommon,emotion,enchantment,fear,mental\" data-pf2-label=\"Warcaller's Chime of Dread DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"27\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"all\">Will</span> save. On a failure, they become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 1} (@Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Frightened]{Frightened 2} on a critical failure). Affected creatures can't reduce their frightened condition below frightened 1 while the chime is ringing. You can Sustain the Activation to sustain the aura, up to a total of 5 rounds. This chime can be used only once per day, whether or not you Sustain the aura.</p>"
